/****************************************************************/
/*                                                              */
/*  Thermodynamic Database                                      */
/*                                                              */
/****************************************************************/

/* Database structure:
   ["Formula", [
       ["state1", [ΔHf°, S°, ΔGf°, Cp°, [Tags]]],
       ["state2", [ΔHf°, S°, ΔGf°, Cp°, [Tags]]],
       ...
   ]]

   ΔHf° = Standard enthalpy of formation (kJ/mol)
   S°   = Standard molar entropy (J/(mol·K))
   ΔGf° = Standard Gibbs free energy of formation (kJ/mol)
   Cp°  = Standard molar heat capacity (J/(mol·K))
   Tags = List of classification tags
   null indicates the datum is not available
   All at 298.15 K (25 °C) and 1 bar

   When a substance has two solid polymorphs (e.g. C graphite / diamond,
   Sn white / grey, CaCO3 calcite / aragonite) the FIRST "s" entry is
   the standard-state form.
*/

%_THERMO_DATA: [
